1 packet Leek
1 packet Gnocchi
200 g Mild Chorizo
1 packet Baby Leaves
1 packet Tomato Paste
1 packet Cream
1 packet Grated Parmesan Cheese
1 sachet Chicken-Style Stock Powder
1 sachet Herb & Mushroom Seasoning
3 cup water
2 tsp brown sugar
1 drizzle olive oil

• Heat a large saucepan over medium-high heat with a generous drizzle of olive oil.
• When oil is hot, cook gnocchi, tossing occasionally, until golden, 6-8 minutes. Transfer to a bowl.
• Meanwhile, finely chop mild chorizo (see ingredients).
TIP: Add extra oil if the gnocchi sticks to the pan.

• Return saucepan to medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil.
• Cook chorizo and sliced leek, tossing, until browned and tender, 4-5 minutes.
• Add herb & mushroom seasoning and tomato paste and cook until fragrant, 1 minute.
• Add chicken-style stock powder, the brown sugar and water and bring to the boil.

• Remove pan from heat, return gnocchi and then add cream (see ingredients) and baby leaves, stirring, until combined. Season to taste.

• Divide creamy chorizo and gnocchi soup between bowls.
• Sprinkle over grated Parmesan cheese to serve. Enjoy!